FLEETADD
  Assign ships to a fleet letter, so the fleet can be used as a group
  designation on navigate, fire, torpedo, and tend.

SYNTAX
  fleetadd <fleet-letter> <ship-spec>[?realm=N][&type=X]
  fleet    <fleet-letter> <ship-spec>[?realm=N][&type=X]

DESCRIPTION
  Sets the fleet letter on every owned ship matching <ship-spec>.
  Once ships carry a fleet letter, that same letter can be used as
  the ship-spec argument to 'navigate', 'fire', 'torpedo', or 'tend'
  to select every ship currently in that fleet — no need to track
  individual uids.

  <fleet-letter> - a single letter a-z or A-Z naming the fleet, or
                    "~" to clear the fleet assignment (return the
                    ships to the null/unassigned fleet)
  <ship-spec>    - which ships to (re)assign:
                      "*"        every owned ship
                      "5"        ship uid 5
                      "0-5"      ship uids 0 through 5
                      "2,14,23"  a comma list of uids
                      "~"        every ship with no fleet assigned
                      "c"        every ship currently in fleet c
                                 (lets you rename/merge a fleet)

  <ship-spec> also accepts the same ?realm=N/&type=X suffix filters
  as 'ship' (see 'info ship'/'info realm'):
    ?realm=N    only ships currently within realm N's bounding box
    ?type=X     only ships of type X -- matches the short type code
                (e.g. "can" for nuc carrier) or a substring of the
                full name

  Fleet assignment has no effect on efficiency, mobility, or combat
  strength — it is purely an organizational grouping, same as wings
  for planes.

  One difference from wings: if a ship joins a fleet and another of
  your ships is already in that fleet at the exact same sector with
  a group-retreat plan set, the joining ship inherits that retreat
  plan. This mirrors 4.4.1's fleet mechanic, though it has no visible
  effect yet in empire5 — retreat execution isn't implemented.

EXAMPLE
  fleetadd c *                put all owned ships into fleet c
  fleetadd b 0-5               put ships 0-5 into fleet b
  fleetadd d ~                 put all unassigned ships into fleet d
  fleetadd e c                 rename/merge fleet c's ships into fleet e
  fleetadd ~ c                 clear fleet c's ships back to unassigned
  fleetadd c *?realm=2&type=can   put your nuc carriers in realm 2 into fleet c
  navigate c jjn                move every ship in fleet c three steps
  fire ship c ship 12           every ship in fleet c fires on ship 12
  torpedo c 12                  every ship in fleet c torpedoes ship 12
  tend oil c 200 15             fleet c tenders 200 oil to ship 15

